<chapter id="using">
<title>Using &krayon;</title>

<sect1 id="basics">
<title>&krayon; Basics</title>

<para>To get you started right away using &krayon;, this tutorial will
guide you step by step in making a finished image. Beneath each step
in this tutorial is a note. This note will explain what the previous
step in the tutorial accomplished.</para>

<para>A red rectangle will outline on each screenshot the object you
will need to push, change, click, etc. for the given step.</para>

<sect2 id="basics_new">
<title>Creating a New Image</title>

<para>When you first start &krayon; (or start a new document after
&krayon; is running), it displays a <guilabel>Choose</guilabel>
dialog. You can choose to create a new image from scratch or from a
template, or open an existing image.</para>

<screenshot>
<mediaobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="unfinished.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>Choose Dialog</phrase></textobject>
</mediaobject>
</screenshot>

<note>
<para>This dialog box is used to:
<orderedlist>
<listitem>
<para>To select the initial template for your new document</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>Open a &krayon; image saved to your hard drive or network.</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>Start &krayon; with a new image.</para>
</listitem>
</orderedlist>
</para>
</note>

<para>Step 1: Click on the <quote><guibutton>Start with an empty
document</guibutton></quote> radio button. Then click on the
<guibutton>OK</guibutton> button.</para>

<screenshot>
<mediaobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="unfinished.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>New Image Dialog</phrase></textobject>
</mediaobject>
</screenshot>

<note>
<para>This dialog box is used to select the size, color mode and
default background color of a new image</para>
</note>

<para>Step 2: All of the defaults in the <guilabel>New
Image</guilabel> dialog are sufficient for our needs. Click on the
<guibutton>OK</guibutton> button.</para>

</sect2>

